'''Uwato Shrine''' (うわとじんじゃ) is a {{jalink|Shinto shrine|Q845945}} located in {{jalink|Gifu Prefecture|Q131277}}, {{jalink|Anpachi District|Q1204320}}, {{jalink|Gōdo Town|Q1203575}}.

It is a candidate shrine (ronsha) for Uwato Shrine of Anpachi District, Mino Province, listed in the {{jalink|Engishiki Jinmyōchō|Q11064932|Engishiki}}. (Another candidate shrine is {{jalink|Uwato Shrine (Anpachi Town)|Q11449527|Uwato Shrine}} “Ubatō-jinja” in {{jalink|Anpachi Town|Q474384}}, Anpachi District.) Under the {{jalink|modern system of ranked Shinto shrines|Q712534|former shrine ranking system}}, it was classified as a gōsha.

=== History and overview ===
*The date of establishment is unknown. During the {{jalink|Edo period|Q184963}}, it was known as Omon Daimyōjin and Okado Daimyōjin.
*Amid the turmoil of the {{jalink|Meiji Restoration|Q8707}} in the early {{jalink|Meiji period}}, the shrine fell into ruin; the shrine buildings also deteriorated around this time, and today only a simple main sanctuary and worship hall remain.
*It is said that the shrine is currently managed by {{jalink|Hiyoshi Shrine (Gōdo Town)|Q11505069|Hiyoshi Shrine}}. According to one theory, in order to protect the sacred object during the chaos of the early Meiji period, the sacred object of Uwato Shrine was transferred to Hiyoshi Shrine.

=== Transportation ===
*About a 15-minute walk from {{jalink|Yōrō Railway|Q11666892}} {{jalink|Hiro-Gōdo Station|Q5769897}}.

