*The date of establishment is unknown. During the {{ill|lt=Edo period|Q184963|WD=Q184963|1=Edo period}}, it was known as Omon Daimyōjin and Okado Daimyōjin.
*Amid the turmoil of the {{ill|lt=Meiji Restoration|Q8707|WD=Q8707|1=Meiji Restoration}} in the early {{ill|UNKNOWN|lt=Meiji period|1=Meiji era|WD=Q3125096}}, the shrine fell into ruin; the shrine buildings also deteriorated around this time, and today only a simple main sanctuary and worship hall remain.
*It is said that the shrine is currently managed by {{ill|lt=Hiyoshi Shrine (Gōdo Town)|Q11505069|WD=Q11505069|lt=Hiyoshi Shrine|1=Hiyoshi Shrine (Gōdo)}}. According to one theory, in order to protect the sacred object during the chaos of the early Meiji period, the sacred object of Uwato Shrine was transferred to Hiyoshi Shrine.

=== Transportation ===
*About a 15-minute walk from {{ill|lt=Yōrō Railway|Q11666892|WD=Q11666892|1=Yoro Railway}} {{ill|lt=Hiro-Gōdo Station|Q5769897|WD=Q5769897|1=Hiro-Gōdo Station}}.

